25|$|A farmer (also {{called an}} agriculturer) is a <b>person</b> <b>engaged</b> <b>in</b> <b>agriculture,</b> raising living organisms for food or raw materials. The term usually applies {{to people who}} do some {{combination}} of raising field crops, orchards, vineyards, poultry, or other livestock. A farmer might own the farmed land or might work as a laborer on land owned by others, but in advanced economies, a farmer is usually a farm owner, while employees of the farm are known as farm workers, or farmhands. However, in the not so distant past, a farmer was a person who promotes or improves the growth of (a plant, crop, etc.) by labor and attention, land or crops or raises animals (as livestock or fish).|$|E
